(50, NULL, '46', 'how-do-i-convert-my-google-ads-smart-campaigns-to-standard-ones', 1, 10, 'How do I convert my Google Ads smart campaigns to standard ones?', '2020-12-10 09:52:37', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><strong>Question:</strong> I\'m trying to figure out how to convert my smart campaigns so I can set a maximum bid for clicks. The smart campaign is setting the bids far too high and I can\'t afford it. <strong>Question:</strong> I set up my first campaign to take advantage of the offer where Google matches up to &pound;120. Never having used Google Ads before, I didn\'t realise it was creating a \"Smart\" campaign. Now it\'s been running for a week or so with less than stellar CTRs, I want to tweak it but don\'t have access to things like Extensions because it\'s not a \"full\" campaign.</p>\r\n<div><strong>Solution</strong>: https://ads.google.com/intl/en_ae/home/tools/keyword-planner/</div>\r\n<p>Add your keywords to the list and click \"CREATE Campaign\" Button.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"384\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"428\" /></p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', NULL, '', '', '0', 0, 0, 1, '2020-09-27 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0);
