(19, 1, 'google-adwords.jpg', 'google-adwords', 9, 1, 'Google Adwords', '2020-12-10 20:05:32', '', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><strong>Google Adwords Dubai</strong></p>\r\n<p>Google AdWords is Google\'s advertising system, where advertisers bid on certain keywords to show their clickable ads on Google search results. Google Certified Agency IMRANONLINE will help your site appear in relevant keyword searches and help your business grow through Google ads. We create effective advertising campaigns for any budget and for any purpose. When people search on Google using one of your keywords, your ad can appear alongside search results. Now focus on an audience that already interests you. Attract more customers to your site and by phone. Advertising online on the Google Network can help you reach the right customers and grow your business. Google Advertising Dubai, Google AdWords Dubai Company, Google AdWords Management Company, PPC Agency</p>\r\n<p><strong>Show your ad on Google today</strong></p>\r\n<p>Google Adwords or Google PPC-SEM ads, Adwords, Pay Per Click, PPC, Select Costs, CTR - digital advertising terms mine. One of the best ways to attract consumers is to advertise on Google or other party sites, which you pay only when someone clicks on them. As a senior PPC company in the UAE, we offer AdWords management services where we will work to increase your ROI on any PPC campaign you choose for all spend that people manage on your behalf. We want to keep in mind the frustration of setting up and studying advertising clubs. A prerequisite for any custom ad campaign may be to offer the best type of ad at the right time. Once the ambitions are in place, we can tailor our strategy and advertising to ensure we reach our target market at the right time and in the right product.</p>\r\n<p>Be visible to these customers when they search for what you have on Google search. You only pay when they visit your site or call. With a search engine market share of over 95%, Google search ads provide a very effective way to reach customers with great intent. People who are close to a purchase decision at the right time and at the right time.</p>\r\n<p>There are 120 million search queries in the United Arab Emirates every day. With so many discoveries, this is an opportunity not to be missed! We create high quality campaigns that work for you. Our digital marketing experts and innovative techniques work together to optimize your campaign and make the right contacts with potential customers.</p>\r\n<p>We do this by creating a Google search advertising campaign that targets the right keywords so you can attract potential customers when they search Google for your product or service. We also provide you with comprehensive reports and data about your campaign so you can continuously analyze the performance of your ads.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Why Google AdWords?</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Attract more customers.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Whether you want to attract new site visitors, make online sales, make phone calls, or return customers for longer, Google AdWords is the best choice.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reach the right people at the right time.</strong></p>\r\n<p>People find your business right on Google when they search for what you have to offer.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Local or international advertising.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Target your ads to customers in specific countries, regions, or cities, or within a certain distance of your business or store.</p>\r\n<p><strong>If you need us, we are here.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Choose how you want to reach customers.</strong></p>\r\n<p>With text search ads, image ads, YouTube video ads, or mobile ads, you have many ways to reach your target customer.</p>\r\n<p><strong>It can be seen all over the web</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Just search on Google.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Search ads appear alongside Google search results when people search for the products and services you offer. You only pay when people click to visit your site or call your business.</p>\r\n<p><strong>You can access customers on devices - the web and apps.</strong></p>\r\n<p>With more than 2 million sites and more than 450,000 apps, AdWords Display Ads show your ad, regardless of your audience.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Share your story</strong></p>\r\n<p>Video ads appear only to the people you want, and you only pay when they see them. In other words, you won\'t spend money promoting people who aren\'t interested in your business.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reach users who like your app.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Public app campaigns help promote your iOS or Android app to billions of Google users - all in one campaign. With Google Machine Learning, you can find the best users and make the most of your budget.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>You only pay for the results.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>No visit no fee</strong></p>\r\n<p>Signing up for Google AdWords is free. You only pay when someone clicks on your ad or calls to visit your site. In other words, when your ad is shown.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Start with any budget.</strong></p>\r\n<p>You set your budget, so your costs will depend on what you want to achieve with your ads. Some companies spend tens of thousands of dollars a month, while some people feel comfortable investing several hundred dollars.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How does AdWords work?</strong></p>\r\n<p>We create your ads and choose keywords that are words or phrases related to your business.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Your ads are running on the Google Network</strong></p>\r\n<p>When people search on Google using one of your keywords, your ad can appear alongside search results. Now focus on an audience that already interests you.</p>\r\n<p><strong>You attract customers</strong></p>\r\n<p>People can simply click on your ad to make purchases or learn more about you. You don\'t even need a website to get started - we\'ll help you create one.</p>\r\n<p><strong>AdWords to reach customers</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Extend reach with the content network</strong></p>\r\n<p>With hundreds of high-quality sites, news pages, and blogs that partner with Google to show AdWords ads, the Google content network can reach users across the web to help drive conversions. To receive a message, select one of the text, image, and video formats.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Search for keywords</strong></p>\r\n<p>The keywords used in your ad will be derived from a comprehensive analysis of the location of your services on the Internet. The results are intended for this phase of the project.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Campaign and Budget Goals</strong> - Campaign goals are metrics that a business wants to achieve based on average clicks, lead cost, conversion rate, and cost per conversion. A maximum monthly advertising budget will be set.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Conversion Strategy</strong> - The conversion strategy determines how a business is converting, such as the type of contact that leads to a click on your ad. It also emphasizes the need to identify specific pages on your site that will serve as the landing page for these ads, and will take steps to accelerate conversions as soon as a visitor arrives at your site.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Keyword List</strong> - The keywords used in your ads will be obtained by analyzing the searches used for your business services. This includes monthly search volume and estimated bid prices. This list will be used as a basis for the specified keyword ad groups during campaign setup.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>What is Google AdWords?</strong></p>\r\n<p>What is AdWords? Google AdWords is Google\'s advertising system, where advertisers bid on certain keywords to show their clickable ads on Google search results. Because advertisers pay for these clicks, this is how Google earns money from search.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Does AdWords work?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Does Google AdWords work? Depending on the competition for your keywords, the goal is to set bids for your company\'s actual conversions and how relevant AdWords can be to your business. For the most part, we believe that Google AdWords is very effective for many types of businesses, as long as they don\'t spend their money on the wrong keywords or write bad, low-click ads.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How much does Google AdWords cost?</strong></p>\r\n<p>There are several factors that can affect the cost of AdWords advertising for your business. Learn all about these costs, how bids work, and how much our AdWords cost?</p>\r\n<p><strong>How do I advertise with Google Adwords?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Businesses can advertise on the Google Network by opening a Google AdWords account. Learn more about making the most of Google AdWords. Or, follow the proven path to AdWords success in the How to Use Google AdWords Infographic section.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How does AdWords bidding work?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The actual position of the ad is determined by the Ad Rank. The highest Ad Rank gets the first ad position. Your actual CPC will be determined by ranking next to the top ad divided by your Quality Score. The only exception to this rule is when you are the only or lowest bidder in the AdWords auction; Then you pay the maximum price per click! AdWords bidding imposes heavy penalties on advertisers who bid low on Quality Score. Conversely, people with higher Quality Scores have higher Ad Rank and.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How does the Google Auction work?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once you\'ve made a query on the Google Network, the search engine processes the request and holds an auction, which will determine the ad position and CPC for each advertiser.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How do I enter the Google Auction?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Your Google ad is eligible to enter the auction when you bid on keywords related to a user\'s search query. Your price and quality and convenience metrics will determine if your ad is eligible to appear on the SERPs.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What\'s entered in the Google Auction?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once you\'ve selected the keywords that the advertiser wants to bid on, Google enters from your account the keyword it considers most relevant to the auction with the maximum bid and associated advertising.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is CPC?</strong></p>\r\n<p>CPC is the amount an advertiser pays each time someone clicks on their AdWords advertisement.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How does CPC work?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Your cost-per-click (CPC) is determined by your keyword\'s competitiveness, maximum cost, and Quality Score. Learn about the most expensive keywords in Google AdWords.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What\'s the average AdWords CPC?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The average AdWords CPC varies by keyword and industry, but is approximately $ 2.32 for the search network and $ 0.58 for the Display Network. Get above the AdWords average here.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is Google\'s Quality Score?</strong></p>\r\n<p>This is a metric used by Google to determine the relevance and usefulness of your ad to the user, based primarily on the ad\'s clickthrough rate, keyword relevance, and landing page quality. The higher your Quality Score, the better: Keywords with a higher Quality Score will save you money and give you a better Ad Rank.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How does Google determine which payment you make?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cost is determined by maximum bid, Quality Score, and keyword competition.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is Google Ad Rank?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Google Ad Rank is the position of a business ad on a search engine page based on a combination of a company\'s maximum bid and Quality Score.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ad Rank versus Quality Score</strong></p>\r\n<p>Your ad will rank higher than the page where your ad appears. Quality Score, on the other hand, is determined by the researcher\'s relevance and interest, and is only part of the ad placement process. As of 2013, Google\'s Quality Score is more valuable as its average Quality Score changes from 7 to 5.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is the ad position in AdWords?</strong></p>\r\n<p>An ad position is the position on the results of a search engine page where the ad appears relative to all other ads.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is the actual cost-per-click?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The actual CPC is the amount an advertiser pays each time a searcher clicks on their ad. This number varies depending on the other advertisers in the auction and is always below the maximum bid.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How does AdWords calculate your actual CPC?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The actual CPC is determined by dividing the next competitor\'s Ad Rank (achievable Ad Rank) by the Quality Score plus $ 0.01.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What are alternative bidding methods?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Alternative bidding methods include CPM and CPA.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is cost-per-thousand-impressions (CPM) bidding?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM) is based on impressions and can be used with cost-per-click (CPC) bidding.</p>\r\n<p><strong>CPC vs. CPM</strong></p>\r\n<p>CPC is the cost of advertising based on the number of clicks received, while CPM is the cost of advertising based on the number of impressions captured. Both methods can be used simultaneously.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What are AdWords keywords?</strong></p>\r\n<p>AdWords keywords are words and phrases that advertisers expect their ads to appear on a search engine results page (SERP) when people search for those products or services. For example, if you sell shoes online, you can bid on keywords like \"Nike sneakers\" and \"moccasins.\" Keyword research is the process of using tools and data to determine which keywords are most likely to drive relevant traffic to your ads and site.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is search engine optimization?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Search engine optimization is the process of using organic techniques to improve the visibility of your site or page on search engine results pages. You can do this by using search keywords in your content so that the search engine can search and display your site faster and more accurately. The authority of the site and your cookie also play a role in your search engine rankings.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How does the Google Display Network work?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Google Display Network (GDN) is a very large network of sites that allows Google to show ads to more than 90% of all Internet users! For advertisers, Display Network clicks generally appear to be cheaper than search network clicks. Depending on the targeting methods you use, your clickthrough rate (CTR) may be higher and your CPA (CPA) may be lower.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How relevant is AdWords advertising?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Ad relevance is an indicator of how well a keyword\'s target bid matches your ads, as well as keywords with your ad message and landing pages. High relevancy for your ads and keywords can improve your click through rate and Quality Score.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How does the Conversion Optimizer work?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Google AdWords Conversion Optimizer is a bid control tool that manages your bids at the keyword level to achieve conversions that are less than or greater than the advertiser\'s specified conversion costs (also called cost-per-action or CPA).</p>\r\n<p><strong>I advertise on Google. Where I should is start?</strong></p>\r\n<p>In&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #626262;\">IMRANONLINE</span>, we analyzed thousands of Google AdWords accounts worldwide in all types of industries. The easiest way to find out how well Google PPC is performing is to measure the performance and spend of similar PPC advertisers in your industry. Fortunately,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #626262;\">IMRANONLINE</span>&nbsp;then got a free tool. Click below to run Google AdWords Grader for free!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '', '', 'COwlNlvaY', 0, 0, 1, '2020-12-05 04:33:02', 0),
